# Refactor Routing and Fix Configuration

## Goal Description
Refactor the frontend to use `react-router-dom` instead of manual state-based routing to fix the broken browser Back button functionality. Also externalize hardcoded URLs in the backend.

## User Review Required
> [!WARNING]
> This refactor will replace the current state-based navigation (`currentView`) with standard URL-based routing. This is a significant structural change for [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/App.tsx).

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend (Client)
#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/App.tsx)
- Remove `currentView` state and manual `pushState` logic.
- Replace conditional rendering with `<Routes>` and `<Route>` from `react-router-dom`.
- Use `useNavigate` instead of custom [navigate](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/App.tsx#49-62) function.
- Ensure `SmoothScroll` wraps the routes effectively.

#### [MODIFY] [index.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/index.tsx)
- Wrap `<App />` with `<BrowserRouter>`.

### Backend (Server)
#### [MODIFY] [auth.js](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/server/routes/auth.js)
- Replace hardcoded `http://localhost:8080` with `process.env.CLIENT_URL`.

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/.env)
- Add `CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:8080`.

